    "question_id" : 2154251,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Yes, int values in an array are initialized to zero. But you are not guaranteed this. Oracle documentation states that this is a bad coding practice.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5843602,
      "reputation" : 96,
      "user_id" : 5743343,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/LNzOc.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Kavishankar Karunakaran",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5743343/kavishankar-karunakaran"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1467961581,
    "creation_date" : 1467961581,
    "answer_id" : 38260784,
    "question_id" : 2154251,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can create a new empty array with your existing array size, and you can assign back them to your array. This may faster than other.\nSnipet: </p>\n\n<pre><code>package com.array.zero;\npublic class ArrayZero {\npublic static void main(String[] args) {\n    // Your array with data\n    int[] yourArray = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9 };\n    //Creating same sized array with 0\n    int[] tempArray = new int[yourArray.length];\n    Assigning temp array to replace values by zero [0]\n    yourArray = tempArray;\n\n    //testing the array size and value to be zero\n    for (int item : yourArray) {\n        System.out.println(item);\n    }\n}\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Result :</p>\n\n<pre><code>0\n0\n0\n0\n0    \n0\n0\n0\n0\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9547068,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 7092669,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5625dfe597ca93ec867e3e3d1bb91882?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Ubeyd",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7092669/ubeyd"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1477857811,
    "creation_date" : 1477857811,
    "answer_id" : 40333055,
    "question_id" : 2154251,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>    int a=7, b=7 ,c=0,d=0;\n    int dizi[][]=new int[a][b];\n    for(int i=0;i&lt;a;i++){\n        for(int q=d;q&lt;b;q++){\n            dizi[i][q]=c;               \n            System.out.print(dizi[i][q]);\n            c++;\n        }\n\n        c-=b+1;\n        System.out.println();               \n    }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>result \n    0123456\n    -1012345\n    -2-101234\n    -3-2-10123\n    -4-3-2-1012\n    -5-4-3-2-101\n    -6-5-4-3-2-10</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 63479,
      "reputation" : 5896,
      "user_id" : 187883,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a8f2a22a57d760fe666f518a8d9f1355?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "NateS",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/187883/nates"
