  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2154251/any-shortcut-to-initialize-all-array-elements-to-zero",
  "title" : "Any shortcut to initialize all array elements to zero?",
  "body" : "<p>In <code>C/C++</code> I used to do </p>\n\n<pre><code>int arr[10] = {0};\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>...to initialize all my array elements to 0.</p>\n\n<p>Is there a similar shortcut in Java?</p>\n\n<p>I want to avoid using the loop, is it possible?</p>\n\n<pre><code>int arr[] = new int[10];\nfor(int i = 0; i &lt; arr.length; i++) {\n    arr[i] = 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
